The paper focuses on developing a system for detecting social interactions using mobile sensing data, which falls under the category of social computing (cs.SI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of mobile phone sensors also relates to mobile computing (cs.MM) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses the analysis of crowd behavior, which could be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SD).
